headlines.description: — Terry Rozier scored 19 points, Miles Bridges added 17 and the Charlotte Hornets beat the Washington Wizards 97-87 on Wednesday night for their fourth straight victory.
headlines.shortLinkText: Hornets beat Wizards 97-87 for 4th straight victory

headlines.description: — Jeremi Grant scored 19 points, Cory Joseph added 18 and the Detroit Pistons rallied to beat the Indiana Pacers 97-89 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Grant, Joseph lead Pistons to 97-89 comeback win over Pacers

headlines.description: — John Collins scored 20 points, Cam Reddish and Kevin Huerter had 19 apiece and the Atlanta Hawks won their third straight game with a 110-99 victory over the Boston Celtics on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Balanced Hawks win 3rd straight, beating Celtics 110-99

headlines.description: — James Harden scored 27 points, LaMarcus Aldridge had 24 and Kevin Durant 23 to help the Brooklyn Nets beat the short-handed Cleveland Cavaliers 109-99 on Wednesday.

events.name: New Orleans Pelicans at Miami Heat

headlines.description: — Jimmy Butler had a triple-double in his return from a sprained right ankle, finishing with 31 points, 10 rebounds and 10 assists in the Miami Heat’s 113-98 victory over the New Orleans Pelicans on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Butler has triple-double in return, Heat top Pelicans 113-98

events.name: Orlando Magic at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — Cole Anthony had 15 points and 10 rebounds, Mo Bamba added 12 points and 11 boards, and the Orlando Magic rallied late in the fourth quarter to defeat the New York Knicks 104-98 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Magic rally late, beat Knicks 104-98 to stop 3-game slide

events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at Milwaukee Bucks

headlines.description: — Giannis Antetokounmpo scored 47 points and Khris Middleton tied Milwaukee’s franchise record for career 3-pointers as the Bucks beat the Los Angeles Lakers 109-102 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Antetokounmpo, Middleton help Bucks defeat Lakers 109-102

headlines.description: — Anthony Edwards scored 16 of his 26 points in the fourth quarter and Karl-Anthony Towns had 22 for the Minnesota Timberwolves in a 107-97 win against the Sacramento Kings on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Edwards closes out Timberwolves' 107-97 win against Kings

events.name: Houston Rockets at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — Lu Dort scored 34 points and the Oklahoma City Thunder beat the Houston Rockets 101-89 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Lu Dort scores 34 points, Thunder beat Rockets 101-89

headlines.description: — It was a shooting slog for much of Wednesday night for the Phoenix Suns, who bricked short jumpers, 3-pointers and just about everything in between.
headlines.shortLinkText: Booker scores 24 points, Suns beat Mavs for 10th straight

events.name: Chicago Bulls at Portland Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — Larry Nance Jr. certainly heard the home fans chanting his name when he sank a pair of free throws with 12 seconds left to help the Trail Blazers beat the Bulls.
headlines.shortLinkText: Lillard rallies Blazers to 112-107 victory over Bulls
